# Form Conventions

## Stack
All forms use **React Hook Form** + **Zod** via `@hookform/resolvers/zod`.

## Schema Location
Place Zod schemas in `lib/schema/` organised by section:
```
lib/schema/
  fc/
    basicInfo.schema.ts
    billingInfo.schema.ts
  index.ts   ← re-exports
```

## Schema Pattern
```ts
// lib/schema/fc/basicInfo.schema.ts
import { z } from "zod";

export const basicInfoSchema = z.object({
  firstName: z.string().min(1, "First name is required"),
  lastName: z.string().min(1, "Last name is required"),
  email: z.string().email("Invalid email address"),
});

export type BasicInfoFormValues = z.infer<typeof basicInfoSchema>;
```

## Form Component Pattern
```tsx
"use client";

import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { basicInfoSchema, BasicInfoFormValues } from "@/lib/schema/fc/basicInfo.schema";
import { Form, FormControl, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormMessage } from "@/components/ui/form";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

export default function BasicInfoForm() {
  const form = useForm<BasicInfoFormValues>({
    resolver: zodResolver(basicInfoSchema),
    defaultValues: { firstName: "", lastName: "", email: "" },
  });

  const onSubmit = async (values: BasicInfoFormValues) => {
    // call apiRoutes.* here
  };

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
        <FormField
          control={form.control}
          name="firstName"
          render={({ field }) => (
            <FormItem>
              <FormLabel>First Name</FormLabel>
              <FormControl>
                <Input {...field} />
              </FormControl>
              <FormMessage />
            </FormItem>
          )}
        />
        <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
      </form>
    </Form>
  );
}
```

## Submission Error Handling
Surface API errors as form-level errors using `form.setError`:
```ts
try {
  await apiRoutes.public.signup(values);
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof ApiError) {
    form.setError("root", { message: error.message });
    // or toast.error(error.message);
  }
}
```

## Rules
- Always co-locate schema with the form's domain section under `lib/schema/`
- Use `z.infer<typeof schema>` to derive the TypeScript type — do not define separate interfaces
- Use shadcn `Form`, `FormField`, `FormItem`, `FormLabel`, `FormControl`, `FormMessage` wrappers for consistent styling and accessibility
